traits.aws.iam#actionPermissionDescription: Grants permission to associate Applications to a StreamGroup
traits.smithy.api#documentation:
If a customer want to start stream sessions with different applications on the same stream group, he needs to
call this API to associate those applications to that stream group beforehand.
Example CLI input
aws gamecast associate-applications --identifier arn:aws:gamecast:us-west-2:123456789012:streamgroup/33gveJpz0 \
    --application-identifiers arn:aws:gamecast:us-west-2:123456789012:application/4VYlL3Me0
Idempotency token.

traits.aws.iam#actionPermissionDescription: Grants permission to disassociate Applications from a StreamGroup
traits.smithy.api#documentation:
If a customer no longer want to start stream sessions with an applications on a stream group, he needs to
call this API to disassociate it from that stream group.
Example CLI input
aws gamecast disassociate-applications --identifier arn:aws:gamecast:us-west-2:123456789012:streamgroup/33gveJpz0 \
    --application-identifiers arn:aws:gamecast:us-west-2:123456789012:application/4VYlL3Me0

Environment variables to the game runtime environments. For example, session specific user profile or resolution/graphics settings.
In theory we support any wine, vulkan, mesa, dxvk, vkd3d environment variables. They are very useful for both
debugging and fine-tuning game performance.
Executable path is a relative path to the game launcher executable.

Save or log file location uri that points to a GameCast owned S3 location that contains the file.
If this is null, it means there is no such file for the stream session.

A list of save file, registry key or log paths that are absolute paths that store game save files when the games
are running on a Windows environment.
Amazon GameCast is a new AWS service that enables customers to build their own game streaming experience.
